e xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vql1665702727392.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vql1665702727392.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vql1665702727392.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vql1665702727392\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      mapping\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify how data types are to be mapped.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vql1665702727392__topic_d52157e1_d52158e1_d52159e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vql1665702727392__p_d52160e1_d52161e1_d52162e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$MSS_PARAMS = mapping : 1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">2</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">11</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">22</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">23</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vql1665702727392__section_tdw_mgh_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d498948e72\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vql1665702727392__ul_kgq_ngh_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vql1665702727392__li_d24701e1_d24702e1_d24703e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vql1665702727392__p_d52166e1_d52167e1_d52168e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>—use the same mapping as the\n                  U1.1 connector</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vql1665702727392__li_d24704e1_d24705e1_d24706e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vql1665702727392__p_d52169e1_d52170e1_d52171e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">2</code>—use the Numeric data type for\n                  N packing codes and SQL Server 7.0 limits (default)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vql1665702727392__li_d24707e1_d24708e1_d24709e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vql1665702727392__p_d52172e1_d52173e1_d52174e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">11</code>—same as\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">mapping=1</code>, but with mapping of money fields (M2) to\n                  Numeric(19,2)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vql1665702727392__li_d24710e1_d24711e1_d24712e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vql1665702727392__p_d52175e1_d52176e1_d52177e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">22</code>—same as\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">mapping=2</code>, but with mapping of money fields (M2) to\n                  Numeric(19,2)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"vql1665702727392__li_d24713e1_d24714e1_d24715e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vql1665702727392__p_d52178e1_d52179e1_d52180e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">23</code>—same as\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">mapping=2</code>, but all date fields are stored in a Date field, by\n                  default. Only applicable for MS SQL 2008 and higher.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/foe1665702727322.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Packing for Microsoft SQL Server</a><p>Uniface packing codes are mapped to MS SQL storage formats (data types).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533134\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533134\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "mapping Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 mapping Specify how data types are to be mapped. USYS$MSS_PARAMS = mapping : 1 | 2 | 11 | 22 | 23 Arguments 1 —use the same mapping as the U1.1 connector 2 —use the Numeric data type for N packing codes and SQL Server 7.0 limits (default) 11 —same as mapping=1 , but with mapping of money fields (M2) to Numeric(19,2) 22 —same as mapping=2 , but with mapping of money fields (M2) to Numeric(19,2) 23 —same as mapping=2 , but all date fields are stored in a Date field, by default. Only applicable for MS SQL 2008 and higher. Related Links Data Packing for Microsoft SQL Server Uniface packing codes are mapped to MS SQL storage formats (data types). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}